##In Wuhan, I cut hair for medical staff

Micro-signal. Meirirenwu

Functional Introduction, light business, understand life.

Shen posted a short video of his haircut to social media and received two unexpected responses: one calling him "bold" and "daring to go to the hospital at this time" , and the other, is For more medical staff to ask him for help.

For his part, he received a phone call from a doctor by accident, didn't hesitate after learning of the other's plight, and was obliged to cut the hair of six doctors in the Laboratory Department of Wuhan No. 4 Hospital in return for a mask and a free medical examination. Can See the former response, he began to fear, decided to enter the hospital before and after carefully disinfection. But that didn't stop him, and he continued to focus on the latter response, systematically docking with hospitals and offering free haircuts to health care workers.

At the moment of the outbreak, in hospitals, where long hair carries the risk of the virus, there is a huge demand for haircuts from medical staff. Shen Jie began to work continuously, within two weeks ran eight or nine hospitals, the most tired time stood for 8 hours a day, cut 65 head. The hair stylist in Wuhan was touched by the efforts of medical workers and was excited that he was finally able to contribute to the fight against the epidemic, but also faced problems such as physical exhaustion, lack of manpower and lack of transport vehicles.

Here is Shen Jie's account.

The hair stylist in Wuhan was touched by the efforts of medical workers and was excited that he was finally able to contribute to the fight against the epidemic, but also faced problems such as physical exhaustion, lack of manpower and lack of transport vehicles.

Here is Shen Jie's account.

By Xiong Renkai
Editor | Xiao Zhu
Operations | Shaorui

1

At noon on February 4th, I got a phone call. He said he was from the Fourth Hospital in Wuhan. His last name is Chen. He's doing the virus test. He and his colleagues need to cut their hair, very anxious, called the other barber shop, no one went, asked me to cut their hair.

I'm from Huanggang. I'm thirty-one. I've had my hair done for 12 years. Four years ago, I returned to Hubei and opened my own shop in Wuhan. Affected by the epidemic, the barber shop can not normally open, the call I was at home, has not been out for more than 10 days.

Many of them haven't had their hair cut in a long time and don't have time to take care of it now, Dr. Chen said, adding that they have to wear several layers of protective clothing for hours, soaking their entire bodies in sweat, not to mention their hair. More importantly, they do a virus test, in case long hair on the ground, may be infected with the virus. The hair was on the doctor's shoe, and the virus could have gotten out of the lab.

At that point, I said yes. I'll be right back with the tools. When I said Yes to him, I really didn't worry a bit. I didn't think of anything. I was watching the news earlier, and the picture showed the doctor wearing such a thick protective suit, and he could hardly walk steadily, so I thought it was not easy for them. Now I can finally do something for them and the fight against the epidemic, especially excited, just want to hurry to give them a haircut, and then go home.

Dr. Chen said he'd pay me. I said I don't have to pay. You can just give me a mask. Put forward this request is I thought to wear a special mask in the hospital, his mask is only one, he said yes, I am also relieved.

Four hospitals not far from my shop, from where I live is only a ten-minute walk, I put on a mask with tools to go. At that time, Wuhan Road people have not so few as now, out of the community will not ask me where to go. I didn't see anyone near the hospital, so I walked around the outside and got to the back door of the hospital where I was supposed to meet Dr. Chen.

I thought that Dr. Chen had been a customer of mine before, so I found myself, and asked him when we met. Dr. Chen said that he had not cut his hair in my shop, but had searched all the barbershops near the hospital on the Internet, and then called one by one, i was the first one to say yes.

He and five colleagues who needed haircuts had changed into white coats, face masks and medical hats.

2

They disinfected me before they cut my hair and gave me a gown, gloves and a mask. Later, I learned that my hard-won respirator had a breathing valve that was not fully insured for hospital use.

I did not go into the ward or the specific department, the haircut is in the cleaning aunt's rest room, there was the laboratory specimen room, there is a mirror, the doctor said health is safer. The lab is full of male doctors, and when I look at their hair, I haven't cut it in, like, two months. They said, no matter what hairstyle before, now cut into short hair, I will give them as required to cut a centimeter long or so.

The inside of the jacket and gloves was muggy and hot, something I had never experienced before. But that's not the biggest problem with cutting a doctor's hair. Since they couldn't take off their masks and the hair around their ears was difficult to cut, I needed one hand to pull the ear, with the fingers of this hand pulling the mask down a bit, and the other hand to cut the hair there.

Shen Jie gave medical staff their first haircut at the cleaning aunt's rest room at Wuhan's Fourth Hospital. Photo / interviewee

After I gave my hair to six doctors, they offered to pay me, and I insisted that they didn't, and they said that there was nothing else we could do for you, so why don't we give you a free checkup. I didn't say yes at first, seeing as how busy they were, but they said it was for your own good, so I agreed.

The physical exam is done in the hospital's outpatient department, where there are now few patients in the regular outpatient department. I had a different impression of the doctor I met during the haircut. In my previous impression, the line to go to the hospital was very long, and the doctors were all very arrogant. But this time, they made me feel very approachable, the service was very good, and kept saying thank you to me, I was very brave, and stuff cookies and self-heating rice in my hand.

On the way home, I thought I do hair so many years, actually ran to the hospital to the doctor haircut, feel very happy.

Before going to the hospital, I left in a hurry without thinking, did not tell the relatives and friends around. At the hospital, I filmed the haircut and made a short video with the doctor. After the short video was posted on social media, many of the comments below said, how dare you go to such a dangerous place as a hospital at this time?

After reading these comments, I was so excited that I finally started to worry and be afraid. I used 84 disinfectant at home and decided that if I went back to the hospital, I would take a hot bath for half an hour before and after.

3

Later I went to Wuhan Four courtyard two times in succession, also recorded a short video to post on the Internet, did not expect comments, likes are particularly many. Many hospitals or out-of-town medical teams send me private messages saying that their medical staff also have haircuts and want me to cut their hair.

But there are difficulties. The first is the problem of manpower, I have two groups of colleagues, a Hankou (region) A wuhan-wide, I call in the group of colleagues together, each of the hospital close to their home.

It didn't work out so well. A lot of the barbers were out of town and went home before the city was shut down. They told the group that they wanted to help, but everyone knew they couldn't get in. There are also some local Wuhan, at first expressed willingness, but later because of family objections and other reasons, there is no way to participate. I'm kind of disappointed.

But slowly, someone else joined in. As far as I know, there are more than a dozen hairdressers doing this kind of thing, most of them are from out of town but have not returned this year. Let's split up and get our hair cut in a hospital near where we live.

In addition to Shen Jie, more and more hairdressers in Wuhan are joining the ranks of free haircuts for medical staff. Photograph: Chinanews.com

Another difficulty is that vehicles are not so easy to find, but the needs of the hospital is still urgent, sometimes they have to contact the vehicle to pick me up. Today, it was snowing in Wuhan, and the Dongxihu District Hospital asked me to cut the hair of their medical staff. I went downstairs to see that an ambulance had come to pick me up. This is my first time in an ambulance.

In the East West Lake District Hospital, the turn of a girl to cut, she said you must cut me good-looking oh! Because tomorrow is a special day. I asked her what it was, and she said it was her birthday. I wished her a happy birthday and told her I would cut it short, but I would cut it nice.

Over the last two weeks, I've gone to seven or eight different places, cutting hair for different medical workers. What impressed me most was the haircut for the Yunnan and Guizhou medical teams that supported the shelter hospitals in the lobby of their hotel.

Shen Jie went by ambulance to get a haircut for the medical staff. Photo / interviewee

With so many people getting their hair cut, I think these out-of-town medical teams are the bravest. They don't ask for anything, just a short haircut. A girl, from Guizhou Province, with waist-length hair, told me straight to shave. I asked her if she'd give it up, and she said, "go ahead, it'll grow back. ". I asked her whether she was afraid to come to Wuhan, and she said that she was afraid, of course. But the whole time, I didn't see her get upset or upset.

I am a hairdresser, see a girl to shave so long hair completely, affirmation is give up. I'm sure she is, too, but given the circumstances, there's really nothing we can do.

It was the hardest day of my life. Except for a meal in the middle, a man stood there for eight hours, cutting the hair of 65 people.

In order to facilitate their work, many female medical workers choose to shave a long head of hair or shaved into a buzz cut. Photo / interviewee

4

I have customers in the south China Seafood Market Wholesale Seafood Business, Xiao Nian I heard about this COVID-19, was very cautious, also saw on the Internet cases are increasing. On the 20th, the News said it would spread from person to person, and I thought it was too scary, so I closed the store.

I started as an apprentice when I was 18, and my dream was to be a celebrity hairdresser, something that many people in the industry dream about, but very few actually do. In order to learn this I spent a lot of money, but also ran a lot of places, to Shanghai, Shenzhen, Hong Kong, to find high-tech hairstylists to learn training.

Then I realized my dream, in Hangzhou, get a job, can give some big star hairstyle. It was so satisfying, I felt like I was at the top of my game. But then I realized that working away from home all the time wasn't a long-term solution, and my parents were getting older and needed to be closer to them to take care of them.

I returned to Wuhan to open a shop, I think in this area to do well, customers are quite recognized me. After closing the shop years ago, I was sent a wechat message from an old customer saying he had to change his shop to get his hair done.

My shop was the first barbershop to close down on the street. It was just before the New Year, when business was at its peak. Customers certainly didn't understand. On the 21st, I went to close the shop, and halfway through the roller shutter, two customers came and asked for a haircut. I said it's too serious now. Can we do it in years? I was scheduled to open on the eighth day of the Lunar New Year. And they're like, "I thought you said twenty-nine was off. " ? Just cut it for me, will you?

I explained a bunch of things, and I said if it's for the best, you can come back in years. They did not listen, I finally pulled down the shutter lock, the scene was quite unpleasant.

My mentality has been more natural, that nothing else, as long as people are healthy and safe. On the 20th, I ordered some masks, called my parents in Huanggang and told them I wasn't going home for the New Year. They said that everything was ready and the room was ready for you. I can only say that I am in Wuhan, it is not safe for them to return to Huanggang, and they are also told to wear masks, wash their hands and ventilate.

After the store closed, I have been at home, the impact of the epidemic, the store of course the pressure is not small, the monthly rent alone on tens of thousands of employees also need to spend.

But I didn't think of paying the doctor for a haircut to make up for it. After the short video went viral, a local newspaper approached me, and the reporter told me that a company had awarded me a "positive energy" award for 10,000 yuan. I thought he was joking, but I didn't believe it until the reporter showed me the certificate.

Shen Jie received the certificate of honor. Photo / interviewee

I immediately asked if I could donate the money directly to the hospital? He said he'd ask around for me, see if I could direct a donation. Finally, the company said that it must transfer the money to my account, and then what to do with it is my business.

I don't want this money. On the one hand, I feel it's an honor to be able to contribute to the fight against the epidemic. On the other hand, I'm also quite an optimistic person. If I lose a little, I'll lose a little. In this situation, my colleagues are all having a hard time, that you're safe and sound above all else.

I love the business of hairdressing. This is a job that brings beauty. When you give someone a good haircut through your work, others will be happy and you will feel a sense of accomplishment. As for the recent haircut, the feeling of accomplishment is completely different, more from the feeling of their own contribution to the strength, these days, I do more and more excited.

But the body is still a little overdrawn, we do this line of work need to stand for a long time, a long time have some cervical spine problems. Recently, the two arms root and cervical vertebrae are very sore. In addition, the hospital haircuts to wear medical gloves, this time for at least five hours, hands kept sweating, and evaporation in gloves, off, the whole hand white.

There's not a lot of barbers out there for paramedics with a demand like this. Look, it's 11:30 at night, and I just had dinner, and I have to meet the hospital after the interview. This period of time is really too busy, and so a little leisure down, I would like to do the first thing is to the enterprise gave me 10,000 dollars to buy into materials, donated to four hospitals.

The physical exam is done in the hospital's outpatient department, where there are now few patients in the regular outpatient department. I had a different impression of the doctor I met during the haircut. In my previous impression, the line to go to the hospital was very long, and the doctors were all very arrogant. But this time, they made me feel very approachable, the service was very good, and kept saying thank you to me, I was very brave, and stuff cookies and self-heating rice in my hand.

On the way home, I thought I do hair so many years, actually ran to the hospital to the doctor haircut, feel very happy.

Before going to the hospital, I left in a hurry without thinking, did not tell the relatives and friends around. At the hospital, I filmed the haircut and made a short video with the doctor. After the short video was posted on social media, many of the comments below said, how dare you go to such a dangerous place as a hospital at this time?

After reading these comments, I was so excited that I finally started to worry and be afraid. I used 84 disinfectant at home and decided that if I went back to the hospital, I would take a hot bath for half an hour before and after.

3

Later I went to Wuhan Four courtyard two times in succession, also recorded a short video to post on the Internet, did not expect comments, likes are particularly many. Many hospitals or out-of-town medical teams send me private messages saying that their medical staff also have haircuts and want me to cut their hair.

But there are difficulties. The first is the problem of manpower, I have two groups of colleagues, a Hankou (region) A wuhan-wide, I call in the group of colleagues together, each of the hospital close to their home.

It didn't work out so well. A lot of the barbers were out of town and went home before the city was shut down. They told the group that they wanted to help, but everyone knew they couldn't get in. There are also some local Wuhan, at first expressed willingness, but later because of family objections and other reasons, there is no way to participate. I'm kind of disappointed.

But slowly, someone else joined in. As far as I know, there are more than a dozen hairdressers doing this kind of thing, most of them are from out of town but have not returned this year. Let's split up and get our hair cut in a hospital near where we live.

In addition to Shen Jie, more and more hairdressers in Wuhan are joining the ranks of free haircuts for medical staff. Photograph: Chinanews.com

Another difficulty is that vehicles are not so easy to find, but the needs of the hospital is still urgent, sometimes they have to contact the vehicle to pick me up. Today, it was snowing in Wuhan, and the Dongxihu District Hospital asked me to cut the hair of their medical staff. I went downstairs to see that an ambulance had come to pick me up. This is my first time in an ambulance.

In the East West Lake District Hospital, the turn of a girl to cut, she said you must cut me good-looking oh! Because tomorrow is a special day. I asked her what it was, and she said it was her birthday. I wished her a happy birthday and told her I would cut it short, but I would cut it nice.

Over the last two weeks, I've gone to seven or eight different places, cutting hair for different medical workers. What impressed me most was the haircut for the Yunnan and Guizhou medical teams that supported the shelter hospitals in the lobby of their hotel.

Shen Jie went by ambulance to get a haircut for the medical staff. Photo / interviewee

With so many people getting their hair cut, I think these out-of-town medical teams are the bravest. They don't ask for anything, just a short haircut. A girl, from Guizhou Province, with waist-length hair, told me straight to shave. I asked her if she'd give it up, and she said, "go ahead, it'll grow back. ". I asked her whether she was afraid to come to Wuhan, and she said that she was afraid, of course. But the whole time, I didn't see her get upset or upset.

I am a hairdresser, see a girl to shave so long hair completely, affirmation is give up. I'm sure she is, too, but given the circumstances, there's really nothing we can do.

It was the hardest day of my life. Except for a meal in the middle, a man stood there for eight hours, cutting the hair of 65 people.

In order to facilitate their work, many female medical workers choose to shave a long head of hair or shaved into a buzz cut. Photo / interviewee

4

I have customers in the south China Seafood Market Wholesale Seafood Business, Xiao Nian I heard about this COVID-19, was very cautious, also saw on the Internet cases are increasing. On the 20th, the News said it would spread from person to person, and I thought it was too scary, so I closed the store.

I started as an apprentice when I was 18, and my dream was to be a celebrity hairdresser, something that many people in the industry dream about, but very few actually do. In order to learn this I spent a lot of money, but also ran a lot of places, to Shanghai, Shenzhen, Hong Kong, to find high-tech hairstylists to learn training.

Then I realized my dream, in Hangzhou, get a job, can give some big star hairstyle. It was so satisfying, I felt like I was at the top of my game. But then I realized that working away from home all the time wasn't a long-term solution, and my parents were getting older and needed to be closer to them to take care of them.

I returned to Wuhan to open a shop, I think in this area to do well, customers are quite recognized me. After closing the shop years ago, I was sent a wechat message from an old customer saying he had to change his shop to get his hair done.

My shop was the first barbershop to close down on the street. It was just before the New Year, when business was at its peak. Customers certainly didn't understand. On the 21st, I went to close the shop, and halfway through the roller shutter, two customers came and asked for a haircut. I said it's too serious now. Can we do it in years? I was scheduled to open on the eighth day of the Lunar New Year. And they're like, "I thought you said twenty-nine was off. " ? Just cut it for me, will you?

I explained a bunch of things, and I said if it's for the best, you can come back in years. They did not listen, I finally pulled down the shutter lock, the scene was quite unpleasant.

My mentality has been more natural, that nothing else, as long as people are healthy and safe. On the 20th, I ordered some masks, called my parents in Huanggang and told them I wasn't going home for the New Year. They said that everything was ready and the room was ready for you. I can only say that I am in Wuhan, it is not safe for them to return to Huanggang, and they are also told to wear masks, wash their hands and ventilate.

After the store closed, I have been at home, the impact of the epidemic, the store of course the pressure is not small, the monthly rent alone on tens of thousands of employees also need to spend.

But I didn't think of paying the doctor for a haircut to make up for it. After the short video went viral, a local newspaper approached me, and the reporter told me that a company had awarded me a "positive energy" award for 10,000 yuan. I thought he was joking, but I didn't believe it until the reporter showed me the certificate.

Shen Jie received the certificate of honor. Photo / interviewee

I immediately asked if I could donate the money directly to the hospital? He said he'd ask around for me, see if I could direct a donation. Finally, the company said that it must transfer the money to my account, and then what to do with it is my business.

I don't want this money. On the one hand, I feel it's an honor to be able to contribute to the fight against the epidemic. On the other hand, I'm also quite an optimistic person. If I lose a little, I'll lose a little. In this situation, my colleagues are all having a hard time, that you're safe and sound above all else.

I love the business of hairdressing. This is a job that brings beauty. When you give someone a good haircut through your work, others will be happy and you will feel a sense of accomplishment. As for the recent haircut, the feeling of accomplishment is completely different, more from the feeling of their own contribution to the strength, these days, I do more and more excited.

But the body is still a little overdrawn, we do this line of work need to stand for a long time, a long time have some cervical spine problems. Recently, the two arms root and cervical vertebrae are very sore. In addition, the hospital haircuts to wear medical gloves, this time for at least five hours, hands kept sweating, and evaporation in gloves, off, the whole hand white.

There's not a lot of barbers out there for paramedics with a demand like this. Look, it's 11:30 at night, and I just had dinner, and I have to meet the hospital after the interview. This period of time is really too busy, and so a little leisure down, I would like to do the first thing is to the enterprise gave me 10,000 dollars to buy into materials, donated to four hospitals.
